.TH "dma_map_host_va" 9 "dma_map_host_va" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dma_map_host_va \- DMA mapping of the given host virtual address.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dma_map_host_va
.BI "(struct hl_device *hdev "  ","
.BI "u64 addr "  ","
.BI "u64 size "  ","
.BI "struct hl_userptr **p_userptr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hdev" 12
habanalabs device structure.
.IP "addr" 12
the host virtual address of the memory area.
.IP "size" 12
the size of the memory area.
.IP "p_userptr" 12
pointer to result userptr structure.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function does the following:
- Allocate userptr structure.
- Pin the given host memory using the userptr structure.
- Perform DMA mapping to have the DMA addresses of the pages.
